Key Match Events: Netherlands defeated South Africa by 13 runs, eliminating South Africa from the World Cup.
Quinton de Kock managed just six off eight balls and lost his wicket to Fred Klaassen.
Brandon Glover's bowling performance was crucial, with no one having a better T20I bowling average for Netherlands.
Roelof van der Merwe's catch to eliminate South Africa was a significant moment.
Post-Match Reflections: Temba Bavuma acknowledged the 'chokers' tag and stated it will remain until South Africa wins a final.
Bavuma looked close to tears as he spoke to the media after the match.
The despondency is exacerbated by the knowledge that South Africa has a powerful side.
The performance was described as timid and scarcely credible in its timidity.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place on a sun-washed Sunday morning in Adelaide.
South Africa's fate was sealed just after dawn back home in South Africa.
